just_use undo_demo.py

# label: EARLY (demo script)
# role: agent tool — end-to-end smoke-test of the undo feature

Small demonstration that exercises the undo feature: make a
move, snapshot state, undo, snapshot state again, confirm
the second snapshot matches the pre-move baseline.

## Status

Verified working end-to-end 2026-04-21 against the live
prod server: merge_hand → split → undo → undo → baseline
restored; action log retains all 4 entries (audit trail
intact). The server-side undo is log-preprocessed — the
action stays in the persisted log, but replay skips it +
its target — and the demo uses the current envelope shape
via `client.send_undo`.

## Usage

```
python3 games/lynrummy/python/undo_demo.py
```

Creates a fresh session, makes a move, prints before/after
hand-size + board-score, issues undo, prints again.

## Pointers

- Depends on: `client.py` in the same dir.
- Memory: `project_one_action_log.md` — undo uses the same
  action log everything else does.
